SIMPLE: snappish
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Snappish
<hw>Snap"pish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Apt to
snap at persons or things; eager to bite; <as>as, a <ex>snapping</ex>
cur</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Sharp in reply; apt to speak angrily or testily;
easily provoked; tart; peevish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The taunting address of a <qex>snappish</qex> misanthrope.</q>
<rj><qau>Jeffrey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Snap"pish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Snap"pish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snappy</ent>⟦br⟧
